The paper presents novel algorithms and implementations for computing the sign function of triangular matrices, which is a fundamental building block in algorithms for computing the sign of arbitrary square real or complex matrices. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Scientific Computing (cs.SC), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
